cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC 

This paper involves the use of reinforcement learning to generate motions for a robot to hold and transport humans in certain rescue or patient care scenarios. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as the focus is on the manipulation of objects and the interaction between robots and humans. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of perception noise, which suggests a possible focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the application of the research to rescue or patient care scenarios suggests a possible focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
